    (273, 'incl_clientDataConfigs', NULL, NULL, 0, 'none', '<p>Without any configuration, Client Data includes all types of values for the&nbsp;current container (where the network request originated) as <strong>TYPE_self</strong>, eg <strong>selected_self</strong>.<br />\r\nForm component values where the&nbsp;<strong>alias</strong>-field is ticked on&nbsp;the current container are included under<strong>&nbsp;clientData -&gt; alias_self</strong>.<br />\r\nForm component values where the&nbsp;<strong>alias</strong>-field is ticked on&nbsp;the parent container are included&nbsp;under&nbsp;<strong>clientData -&gt; alias_parent</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the current container is a grid, the last clicked record&#39;s item values with aliases are included under&nbsp;<strong>clickedLast_self</strong>, and the primary key values of the selected records are included in&nbsp;<strong>selected_self</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Client Data also includes any query parameter values in the browser URL, under&nbsp;<strong>query_params</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Client Data that is not included by default for use on eg. myContainer&#39;s events, must be specified in myContainer&#39;s <strong>configs </strong>field - see the <strong>Specify in Container Configs</strong> column below.<br />\r\nNote, add the configs to the container where the event is triggered, not the target container.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If a container is reused and loaded (visible) in the view more than once, it is not possible to get each instance&#39;s clientData. The workaround for now is to duplicate the container with another name.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A popup/window container&apos;s parent is the container referenced by its port (if set).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Configs can also be set on dropdowns, for use in eg. the SQL underlying the dropdown list.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Arial">The content of the <strong>configs </strong>field is processed as a one dimensional JSON array, but do not include the surrounding curly braces ({ }), eg the following is valid:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Arial"><strong>&quot;alias&quot;: &quot;myForm&quot;,<br />\r\n&quot;selected&quot;: &quot;parent, myGrid&quot;,<br />\r\n&quot;gridFilter&quot;: &quot;myGrid&quot;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>Client Data Type</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px"><strong>What is Returned</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Specify in Container Configs</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Use in Filter / SQL</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>alias</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px">Values of items that have an alias (pef_item.alias=1).</td>\r\n			<td>&quot;alias&quot;:&quot;myForm, myGrid&quot;<br />\r\n			<em>(note, <strong>&quot;alias&quot;:&quot;self, parent&quot;</strong> is included by default)</em></td>\r\n			<td>:alias_myForm_company_id<br />\r\n			:alias_myGrid_selectEnum<br />\r\n			:alias_self_first_name<br />\r\n			:alias_parent_ClientID</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>selected</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px">All the primary key values of records that are selected/checked&nbsp;in either a grid or tree container.</td>\r\n			<td>&quot;selected&quot;:&quot;parent, myGrid, myTree&quot;</td>\r\n			<td>:selected_self_0_myPkField<br />\r\n			:selected_parent_0_id<br />\r\n			:selected_myTree_1_pkey</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>clickedLast</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px">Values of all items that have an alias of the last clicked record in the target grid or tree container.</td>\r\n			<td>&quot;clickedLast&quot;:&quot;parent, myGrid&quot;<br />\r\n			<em>(note, <strong>&quot;clickedLast&quot;:&quot;self&quot;</strong> is included by default)</em></td>\r\n			<td>:clickedLast_parent_id<br />\r\n			:clickedLast_myGrid_company_id</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>formData</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px">Values of all fields on a form container.</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>:formData_parent_name</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>pkey</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px">Primary key values of the current record.<br />\r\n			Available for container dropin types that have a single current record (eg dibForm).</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>:pkey_myContainer_myPk<br />\r\n			:pkey_self_id</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>gridFilter</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px">The filter values as provided by the user in a grid&#39;s filter boxes.</td>\r\n			<td>&quot;gridFilter&quot;:&quot;myGrid. myGrid2&quot;</td>\r\n			<td>:gridFilter_self_name<br />\r\n			:gridFilter_myGrid_company_id</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>query_params</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px">The query parameters present in the current URL, eg /nav/myGrid?<strong>filter_name=jack&amp;filter_last_name=sprat</strong></td>\r\n			<td><em>(only available for current URL)</em></td>\r\n			<td>:query_params_name<br />\r\n			:query_params_last_name</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>activeFilter</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px">Name of the active filter on a particular container or subcontainer component.<br />\r\n			This name can be used as eg a parameter in PHP in calls to&nbsp;<strong>Crud::read()</strong>. The Excel Export button requires the config if the export is done from a grid with a filter.</td>\r\n			<td>&quot;activeFilter&quot;:&quot;myGrid&quot;</td>\r\n			<td>:activeFilter_myContainer</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>prompt</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px">The user&#39;s last reply to the prompt function. This is only available on the first request, and is thereafter&nbsp;removed.</td>\r\n			<td>(included automatically)</td>\r\n			<td>:prompt</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width:107px"><strong>custom</strong></td>\r\n			<td style="width:655px">Custom values set by calling set-custom action, eg<br />\r\n			<strong>shared.action.set-custom?xxx=Employee&amp;zzz=@{value_self_selectEnum)&nbsp;</strong><em>(set global values)</em><br />\r\n			<strong>shared.action.set-custom?containerName=staffForm&amp;position=Employee&nbsp; </strong><em>(set container specific values)</em></td>\r\n			<td>(included automatically)</td>\r\n			<td>:custom_global_xxx<br />\r\n			:custom_global_zzz<br />\r\n			:custom_staffForm_position</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', NULL, 1, 'dib', NULL, NULL, 'doc273-dib'),
