    (287, 'incl_sqlQueryParams', NULL, NULL, 0, 'none', '<h2>Server-side User Parameters</h2>\r\n<p>When a user logs-in successfully, Dropinbase stores values in the PHP session for this user.<br>These values are available as query parameters using the <strong>:dibUser_</strong> prefix. They are also available in PHP in the <strong>DIB::$USER </strong>array.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>See ~nav(dibexSqlParams, SQL Parameters)~ for more information about where parameters can be used.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Note, since these values originate from the server and are linked to the logged-in user, they are safe and useful for limiting records for permission purposes.</p>\r\n<p>By default, a query like the following is used to obtain values. The values can be adjusted in the&nbsp;<strong>DibUserParams.php</strong> class in the <strong>/configs</strong> folder.\r\n<br>For more specific business rules, the official Dropinbase dibAuthenticate dropin can be copied to your projects /dropins folder and adjusted as neccessary.</p>\r\n<pre>\r\n<p>SELECT l.id, l.username, l.perm_group, l.admin_user, l.email, l.test_user, l.first_name, l.last_name, l.default_url, l.session_version,&nbsp;\r\n<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; l.pef_security_policy_id, l.login_expiry, l.login_group_expiry, l.language, l.larger_font, s.name as policyName, l.supplier_code, l.dib_username<br>FROM `pef_login` l&nbsp;<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; INNER JOIN pef_security_policy s ON l.pef_security_policy_id = s.id&nbsp;<br>WHERE l.id = :loginId</p>\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n<p><code>SELECT id, name FROM test_staff WHERE email = <strong>:dibUser_email</strong></code></p>\r\n<p>In many Dropinbase installations, developers add a foreignkey field (eg <strong>staff_id</strong>) to the&nbsp;<strong>pef_login </strong>table<br>and then use&nbsp;<strong>DibUserParams.php</strong> to adjust the query above to include this field which makes it available in User parameters. (Note, for demo puposes the official Dropinbase DibUserParams.php file sets a staff_id value outside the SELECT statement).</p>\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n<p><code>SELECT id, name FROM test_staff WHERE id = <strong>:dibUser_staff_id</strong></code></p>\r\n<p>This then becomes the main means of implementing permissions where users may only see certain data.</p>\r\n<strong>Remember to clear affected generated code, and to login as relevant users, to test changes.</strong>\r\n\r\n<h2>Other Dropinbase Parameters</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>:dibDateTime</strong> - date(\'Y-m-d H:i:s\')</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div><strong>:dibDate</strong> - date(\'Y-m-d\')</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div><strong>:dibTime</strong> - date(\'H:i:s\')</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div><strong>:dibIp </strong>- DibApp::getRealIpAddr()</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div><strong>:dibSessionIdMd5</strong> - md5(session_id())</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div><strong>:dibUniqueId</strong> - cryptographic strong unique random number tied to a user session and set in Authenticator.php; never sent to the browser.</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n<p><code>SELECT id, name FROM test_staff WHERE updated &lt;=&nbsp;<strong>:dibDate</strong></code></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 'dib', NULL, NULL, 'doc287-dib'),
