    (113, 276, 348, 35, 'none', 'General', 'Configuration', NULL, '<p>Preloads the JavaScript for the specified action into memory, ensuring it is available for use later. This is particularly useful for actions that need to be available after a user\'s session expires, or if they have signed out of the application.</p>\n<h4>Parameters:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>submitUrl</strong> (string): The URI of the action to load, for example, <code>shared.action.set-value</code>.</li>\n<li><strong>.containerName</strong> (string): The name of the container to send with the request for permission purposes to retrieve the action.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Example:</h4>\n<div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>\n<div>shared.action.cache-action?containerName=myContainer&amp;submitUrl=shared.action.set-value</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'dce113-dib'),
    (114, 276, 349, 55, 'none', 'General', NULL, NULL, '<p>Deselects all selected records in the specified container.</p>\n<h4>Parameters:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>containerName</strong> (string): The name of the container, for example, <code>self</code>, <code>parent</code>, or <code>myGrid</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Example:</h4>\n<div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li>shared.action.clear-selection?containerName=myContainer</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'dce114-dib'),
    (115, 276, 350, 295, 'none', 'General', NULL, NULL, '<p>Sets the title of a popup window/dialog.</p>\n<h4>Parameters:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>containerName</strong> (string): The name of the container.</li>\n<li><strong>title</strong> (string): The new title for the window (url-encode if executed client-side)</li>\n<li><strong>portItemAlias</strong> (string, optional): The port alias, if applicable.</li>\n<li><strong>titleTranslationKey</strong> (string, optional): The localization translation key, if applicable.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Example:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>shared.action.set-window-title?containerName=myPopupForm&amp;title=the%20new%20title</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'dce115-dib'),
    (116, 348, 351, 10, 'none', 'General', 'Configuration', NULL, '<p>Ability to display table rows in a tree format, based on a foreign-key field in the table that facilitates a recursive relationship.</p>\n<p>Here the <strong>manager_id </strong>field in the <strong>test_staff </strong>table is used.</p>\n<p><strong>Notes:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Most typical grid container settings (eg multiselect=true) work for treegrids, except inline-editting of records.</li>\n<li>See notes under Configuration related to the use of container filters.</li>\n</ul>', '<h3>Container Configuration:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Model</strong>: Table/Custom (does not work with SQL queries yet) ***</li>\n<li><strong>Table</strong>: select a table that contains a single foreign key field that references the table\'s primary key</li>\n<li><strong>Tree Data Parent Link</strong>: select the foreign key field that is used to facilitate the tree structure (recursive relationship) in the table between records.</li>\n<li>TreeGrids can have any layout, but a&nbsp; <strong>contentFor</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;component named<strong> \'columns\' </strong>must be present somewhere.<br>Any grid columns must be descendants of the <strong>columns</strong>&nbsp;item.<br>Drag and drop fields to the <strong>columns&nbsp;</strong>item from the&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Field List</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;in the Component Tree (use the <strong>Refresh </strong>button to reload fields if necessary).</li>\n<li>The Field name and Item name of components that are bound to fields must be the same.</li>\n<li>The <strong>Order No </strong>field (Pg2 in Designer) of grid columns must have unique values to ensure columns and column headers align.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>*** If selecting \'Custom\' (in <strong>Model</strong>), then also provide <strong>Crud Store Controller</strong> (see the help for this field for more info).</p>\n<h3>Item Configuration:</h3>\n<p>Add the following Item Settings to the item that must contain the tree-row expander icon (in our example it is the \'id\' column).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>treeControls = <code>true</code></li>\n<li>cellAttr = <code>style="padding-top:4px;display:flex;flex-direction:row"</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Root (First Level) Filter Criteria:</h3>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">NOTE:</span> implementing container filters on trees applies to all records, which is not useful in most cases. To apply custom filtering to records other than the first level (see below), override the generated code with your own by using a <strong>Crud Store Controller</strong>.</p>\n<p>By default, the first level of nodes is determined by the following criteria:</p>\n<p><strong>[Tree Data Parent Link Field] IS NULL</strong><br>for eg&nbsp;<strong>parent_id IS NULL</strong></p>\n<p>To specify alternative criteria, add a Container Setting record, using&nbsp;<strong>treeRootCriteria </strong>as name, eg:</p>\n<p>treeRootCriteria = <code>client.status = \'new\'</code></p>', NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'dce116-dib'),
    (117, 269, 353, 15, 'eleutheria', 'General', 'Configuration', NULL, '<p>Filters can be added to forms in exactly the same way as with other containers.</p>\n<p>Filter criteria is normally set to return a single record based on a selected value, but the filter can also return many records, allowing the user to scroll through a subset of records only. Note, the latter is not secure since a hacker can easily run a request excluding the \'activeFilter\' parameter - use container permissions to secure records with criteria.</p>\n<p><strong>Ports that Change the URL</strong></p>\n<p>Notice however that form containers opened with ports present a problem if the port changes the URL. By default, the record displayed in a form is determined by the primary key in the URL. Since this may clash with the defined filter, it is highly advisable to configure the port NOT to change the URL.</p>\n<p>When Dropinbase detects a primary key definition in the URL, as well as a filter on a form, it attempts to fetch the record by applying both criteria. When this criteria combination returns no records, it attempts fetching records using only the filter criteria.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'dce117-dib'),
    (118, 277, 356, 30, 'eleutheria', 'General', NULL, NULL, '<h3>Integration with the Dropinbase framework</h3>\n<div>Dropinbase functions can be executed from within the iframe template, by including the TemplateActions.js library in your .html file.</div>\n<ul>\n<li><code>dibCommon.goTo(containerName, portAlias, changeUrl, urlQueryString) </code>&nbsp; &nbsp;- opens a container. Note, use \'\' for empty values, not null</li>\n<li><code>dibCommon.startAction(submitUrl, containerName, responseType, clientData, additionalParams)</code> &nbsp; - calls a client-side action, or a server-side controller function and handles the response. Note, a hidden button with a matching URI is required in the Designer on the named container.</li>\n<li><code>dibCommon.showMessage(message, msgType=\'dialog\', duration=2000)</code> - displays a toast message</li>\n<li><code>dibCommon.clearUrlSearch(containerName, portAlias=\'\')</code> - clears the url query string when a search string is not specified.</li>\n<li><code>dibCommon.env.xxx</code> - gets value xxx configured in /configs/Environment.php,&nbsp;eg dibCommon.env.user_fullname.</li>\n<li><code>dibCommon.messagingService.updateAngular</code> -&nbsp;repaints the browser window. Used if actions change elements that require it.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also see the ~nav(dibexActionEmitEvent)~ action that demostrates how to execute functions in the iframe from the Dropinbase framework.</p>\n<h3>Security</h3>\n<p>The <strong>dibCommon.startAction</strong> function is used to execute a Dropinbase URI.</p>\n<p>Simply create a hidden button on the iframe container linked to an item event with the same URI.</p>\n<p>For an additional layer of security and/or item-level permissions on the event, also add the <strong>itemEventId </strong>parameter specifying the <strong>dibuid </strong>value of the item event. Also add <strong>$itemEventId</strong> (with no default) as parameter to the PHP controller function.</p>\n<p>View source of the below iframe (<strong>/dibExamples/templates/dibexiFrameDropinbaseFunctions.html)</strong>&nbsp;for details.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'dce118-dib');
