    (4348, 'comment13', NULL, 173, 25, 4347, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'There are various types of <b>Container Events</b> that can be triggered in the browser/client (eg <b>load</b>, <b>create</b>, <b>update</b>, etc.) or on the server (eg <b>before update</b>, <b>after delete</b>, <b>before readmany</b>, etc).\n<br>Client events can call client-side or server-side code, and server-side events can call server-side code or return actions to be performed in the browser/client.\n<br>\n<br>\n<b>Table Events</b>, eg <b>bu</b>(before update) or <b>ac</b>(after create) occur with containers that are linked to database tables.\n<br>You may have 3 forms and one updatable grid, all linked to the same table. Any data changes performed by these containers will trigger the same events.\n<br>\n<br>\nSee the examples for more details.', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'mysql', NULL, NULL, 'fixed', 'standard', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'CRUD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 'other', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'nowrap', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 15, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'field', 0, 'david', '2022-10-07 11:56:27', NULL, 'i4348-dib'),
