    (4848, 'comment22', NULL, 197, 25, 4847, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<b>Flex Grow, Flex Shrink, Flex Base (CSS: flex)</b>\n<br>\nSizes a single element in the main direction set by its parent, steered by the three arguments:\n<br><b>flex: grow shrink base</b>\n<br>\n<br><b>base</b> - the base size of the item along the main direction.\n<br><b>grow</b> and <b>shrink</b> - proportional decimal values/weights by which items grow to fill available space, or shrink to keep all items within parent borders.\n<br> \n<br><b>base</b> can be one of the following:\n<ul>\n<li>a fixed value measured by <b>px | % | calc | em | rem | vw | vh</b></li>\n<li><b>auto</b> - use the item\'s width/height property (depending on main direction)\n    <br>if the corresponding width/height value is also set to <b>auto</b> then the item\'s content determines the base value</li>\n</ul>\n<b>How does it work?</b>\n<br>\n<br>Firstly, items are given their base width.\n<br>Then, if there is space left within the parent,\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; - each item with <b>grow</b> not 0 is allocated available space in proportion to this relative value\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; - ie, \'fill space if available, proportionally\'\n<br>else if items overlap their parentâs borders, \n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; - each item with <b>shrink</b> not 0 and <b>grow</b> = 0 is shrunk proportionally to keep all items within borders.\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; - ie, \'shrink if necessary, proportionally\'\n<br>\n<br>\n<b>Notes:</b>\n<ul>\n<li>The weights are relative to other itemsâ <b>grow</b> and <b>shrink</b> values.<br>If for eg. item Aâs <b>grow</b> value is 1, Bâs is 2, then for each 100px extra allocated to A, B gets 200px. Same for <b>shrink</b>.</li>\n<li>If any of base, grow or shrink values are specified in Dropinbase, then defaults are set for other values that are not specified:</li>\n<ul>\n   <li>The default for <b>grow</b> is 0</li>\n   <li>The default for <b>shrink</b> is 1</li>\n   <li>The default for <b>base</b> is 0%</li>\n</ul>\n\n<li>Setting an item\'s <b>width/height</b> has no effect unless base is <b>auto</b>.</li>\n\n<li>Setting <b>max-width/max-height/min-width/min-height</b> prevents it from growing/shrinking further.\n<br>If a group of large items all have <b>shrink</b> = 0, they will overlap their parent\'s borders.\n<br>You could set the parentâs css overflow attribute to make scroll bars appear (overflow:auto), or hide the overlapping content (overflow:hidden).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<br>More info: <a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex\'>https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex</a>', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'mysql', NULL, NULL, 'fixed', 'standard', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'CRUD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 'other', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'nowrap', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 15, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'field', 0, 'david', '2023-02-23 16:59:46', NULL, 'i4848-dib'),
