    (5253, 'spanExplanation2', NULL, 210, 95, 5250, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The <b>Submit Url</b> field in Item and Container Events can have Fill In values.\n<br>Since clientData is sent to the server and is normally sufficient for server-side actions, Fill In values are often used for client-side actions.\n<br>\n<br>The button below has the following string in the item event\'s <b>Submit Url</b> field:\n<br><b>\'shared.action.set-value?dibexDibNgServicesForm.first_name=&#64;&#123;clickedLast_dibexDibNgServicesGrid_first_name&#125;\'</b>\n<br>\n<br>It will set the first_name field on the form to the first_name of the last clicked record in the grid.\n<br>Again, these values are resolved and then the action is performed. Off-course multiple values can be set using the & operator in the action string.\n<br>The <b>set-value</b> action does not require the target item to have an alias.\n<br>Note, Fill Ins are available for any string in the Submit Url fields (item events, container events, server-side actions, etc).', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'mysql', NULL, NULL, 'fixed', 'standard', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'CRUD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 'other', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 20, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'field', 0, 'david', '2023-03-22 17:51:28', NULL, 'i5253-dib'),
    (5254, 'sectionSelectValues', 'Select Values', 210, 82, 5206, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'mysql', NULL, NULL, 'fixed', 'standard', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'CRUD', 'overflow:auto !important;', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 'other', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'column', NULL, 'flex-start', 'flex-start', NULL, '10px', 0, 1, '0%', NULL, NULL, 75, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'field', 1, 'david', '2023-03-17 16:37:38', NULL, 'i5254-dib'),
    (5255, 'span9', NULL, 210, 95, 5249, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When the Port is set on a component (normally a button), the <b>Expression</b> field can contain a query string that will be added to the URL.\n<br>\n<br>The button below has the following string in the <b>Expression</b> field: \n<br><b>\'?primary_id=&#64;&#123;value_self_staffId&#125;&dibexStaffForm.selectedPosition=&#64;&#123;value_dibexDibNgServicesGrid_positionFilter&#125;\'</b> \n<br>\n<br>These values are resolved and then added to the URL when the popup form is opened. \n<br>The <b>primary_id=</b> part navigates to the selected Record. \n<br>The <b>dibexStaffForm.selectedPosition=</b> part sets a value on the popup. Note, to make this work <b>selectedPosition</b> has an alias and is an unbound field. \n<br>Bound fields (like first_name) obtain their values from the data-source request, or from defaults (on new records).', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'mysql', NULL, NULL, 'fixed', 'standard', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'CRUD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 'other', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'field', 0, 'david', '2023-03-22 17:47:09', NULL, 'i5255-dib'),
    (5256, 'cardFormDefaults', 'Form Defaults', 210, 21, 5206, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'mysql', NULL, NULL, 'fixed', 'standard', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'CRUD', 'overflow:auto !important;', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 'other', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'column', NULL, 'flex-start', 'flex-start', NULL, '10px', 1, 1, '0%', NULL, NULL, 90, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'field', 1, 'david', '2023-03-17 17:35:11', NULL, 'i5256-dib'),
    (5257, 'spanExplanation3', NULL, 210, 95, 5256, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<b>Form Defaults</b> can be set on Form Components, and they are resolved on any type of container where you can include a Form Component (form, grid, plain, etc).\n<br>On form and editable grid containers, they are resolved only when a new record is opened (set <b>?record=new</b> in the URL on forms).\n<br>On any other container type, and on editable grids but not under \'columns\', they are resolved when the container is opened.\n<br>On editable grids showing related records on forms via a filter, <b>Form Defaults</b> are often used to insert the value of the foreign key field.\n<br>\n<br>On the grid, the following fields have form defaults:\n<br>Filter Position: <b>Employee</b> - <i>hard-coded value</i>\n<br>Join Date: <b>&#64;&#123;dibDate&#125;</b>\n<br>Position: <b>&#64;&#123;value_self_positionFilter&#125;</b>\n<br>\n<br>On the form, the following field has a default:\n<br>Position: <b>&#64;&#123;value_dibexDibNgServicesGrid_positionFilter&#125;</b>\n<br>\n<br>The following inputs are on this \'plain\' container and are therefore resolved when the container first loads:', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'mysql', NULL, NULL, 'fixed', 'standard', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'CRUD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 'other', NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 20, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'field', 0, 'david', '2023-03-23 14:58:37', NULL, 'i5257-dib'),
